BREAST-COMPOSITION: fibro fatty and glandular breast parenchyma (ACR C)
FINDINGS: A well-defined, smooth mass with spiculated margins is observed in the upper outer quadrant of the breast. This finding suggests a probably benign lesion (BIRADS 3). Additionally, multiple small, punctate calcifications are noted scattered throughout the breast parenchyma. No significant architectural distortion or suspicious features are identified. Skin and nipple appear normal. No significant axillary adenopathy is observed.
